info.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued June 24 at 4:06AM CDT until June 24 at 9:00AM CDT by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM CDT THIS MORNING... * WHAT...Visibility less than one mile in dense fog. * WHERE...Southern Lake and Carlton and South St. Louis Counties. This includes the Tribal Lands of the Fond du Lac Band. * WHEN...Until 9 AM CDT this morning. * IMPACTS...Hazardous driving conditions due to low visibility. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The lowest visibilities will be found within a few miles of Lake Superior. Visibility conditions improve significantly inland, away from the lake.
info.instruction: If driving, slow down, use your headlights, and leave plenty of distance ahead of you.
